The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Healthy rise in Magma profit
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Healthy rise in Magma profit
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, Oct. 12: Magma Fincorp Ltd has reported a 67 per cent growth in profit after tax at Rs 24.39 crore during the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 14.59 crore in the year-ago period.         
	A buoyant automobile market helped the asset finance firm to increase its disbursements by 28 per cent to Rs 1,139 crore.         
	Our business has shown strong growth in a majority of products resulting in a 28 per cent growth in disbursement and a 67 per cent rise in profit, vice-chairman Sanjay Chamaria said. We have also improved our performance in loan recovery. The firms revenue grew to Rs 378.4 crore from Rs 323.9 crore a year ago.         
	Net interest margin improved to 5.4 per cent from 5.1 per cent at the end of first half of 2009-10.         
	Well now concentrate on growing volumes by increasing the share of high-yield products such as tractor financing, he said.                                                                                                                                       
